text:
The thing about cave spiders are that their poison won't kill you, it's their attacks that will and their attacks aren't that dangerous, it's the poison that is, so you have a monster that applies a continuous never ending debuff on you that deals almost no hit damage and the only way to get rid of it is by escaping or killing the spider, in this case, Gura could have easily killed it as she had enough time for 2 or 3 heavy axe swings and then place down some blocks to block the closest path to the spawner. At the end of the day, lack of planning or may i say horrible planning is what got them both killed and made them lose it all. However they may have still had a chance to reach it if they speed ran it, say if they have a discord, someone could have put the screenshot in one of the channels, allowing them to easily follow it without reading chat and having to remember. You may even argued that none of it would have happened if they didn't approach the spawner in an aggressive manner and destroyed it right away. Cave spider spawners due to the debuff and their what i assume to be 1x1 shape and ability to climb walls would be a bit trickier to deal with in terms of xp farming and would hurt if you get hit by them and as far as i know, their loot pool isn't that different if not identical to regular spiders. As for the second death, she should have used her pickaxe to destroy the train tracks to have enough space to put down another block

What i'm trying to say is, they are horrible at the game
